<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Consider the following code</p>

&lt;?php
class Test {
    public function argSimReturn(array $arg1, array $arg2, $arg3)
    {
        return $arg1;
    }
}
?&gt;

<p>Generated XML looks like below</p>

<p>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt;
</p>

<p>But arguments arg1 and arg2 can be returned as</p>

<p></p>

<p>Because they are explicitly declared as array in the method signature.</p>

